question_text:
Write a function that determines whether two input vectors are orthogonal. 
The function should take two vectors of equal length as input and return a logical value:
 true if the vectors are orthogonal, and false otherwise.
 Do not use any built-in MATLAB functions for vector operations
 (except for basic arithmetic operations).

Write a function that determines whether a given set of 2D vectors forms a basis for \(\mathbb{R}^2\). 
The function should take a \(2 \times 2\) matrix as input, where each column represents a vector, and 
return a logical value: \texttt{true} if the vectors form a basis for \(\mathbb{R}^2\), and \texttt{false} otherwise. 
Do not use any built-in MATLAB functions for matrix operations (except for basic arithmetic operations).

Complete the following function that projects a vector onto a subspace 
spanned by an orthonormal basis

Complete the following function that implements the Gram-Schmidt process
 to orthogonalize a set of vectors

Write a function that takes a list of vectors and determines if they form an orthogonal basis for \(\mathbb{R}^n\). 
Assume the vectors are in \(n\)-dimensional space. 
The function should return a boolean indicating whether the vectors form an orthogonal basis.
